<section class="page-hero page-hero--compact">
  <p class="eyebrow">Reference architecture</p>
  <h1>Two tracks, one policy surface.</h1>
  <p>The production adapter targets Microsoft Entra Verified ID. The Aries lab remains a separate test harness for ACA-Py, DIDComm, AnonCreds, mediator flows, and wallet interoperability.</p>
</section>

<section class="band band--white">
  <div class="architecture-grid">
    <article class="track-card track-card--production">
      <span class="track-label">Microsoft production path</span>
      <h2>Entra ID + YubiKey + Verified ID</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>MSAL client-credentials access token for the Request Service REST API.</li>
        <li>Issuer request endpoint for credential offers and callbacks.</li>
        <li>Verifier request endpoint for presentations and authorization decisions.</li>
        <li>Callback events captured as redacted audit records.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="track-card track-card--lab">
      <span class="track-label">Aries interoperability lab</span>
      <h2>ACA-Py + Aegis ID mobile app + VON</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Docker Compose lab for mediator, issuer, verifier, and optional dev ledger.</li>
        <li>Shell scripts for invitations, schemas, credential definitions, issuance, and proofs.</li>
        <li>Localhost admin APIs only; public tunnels are lab-only and need hardening.</li>
        <li>No production dependency on the lab ledger or DIDComm agent.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="band band--ink">
  <div class="console-panel">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Demo API</p>
      <h2>Local adapter checks</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="demo-actions">
      <button class="button button--secondary" data-demo-action="issue">Create Issuance Offer</button>
      <button class="button button--secondary" data-demo-action="verify">Create Presentation Request</button>
      <button class="button button--secondary" data-demo-action="aries">Check Aries Lab</button>
    </div>
    <div class="demo-result-grid" data-demo-result hidden></div>
    <pre class="demo-output" data-demo-output>{
  "verifiedIdMode": "{{microsoftMode}}"
}</pre>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="band band--light">
  <div class="policy-block">
    <p class="eyebrow">Presentation policy</p>
    <pre>{{json policy}}</pre>
  </div>
</section>
